    {
      "id": "69075f5c416568cf8e2147704549209622719b83",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2016-03-29 21:50:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nOleg, \n\nIt looks like SETUP and CLEANUP are no-ops in autotest. So, this shouldn't change current test suite behavior. \n\nAlso, the following just seem wrong. Do you think we should fix them with this patch?\nsanityn.sh:CLEANUP=${CLEANUP:-:}\nsanity.sh:CLEANUP=${CLEANUP:-:}\nsanity.sh:SETUP=${SETUP:-:}\nsanityn.sh:SETUP=${SETUP:-:}",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "51e9addb04d306da1996f19ab49be323ff000994",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-03-29 21:54:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames, \":\" is the no-op operator in shell, so those lines are fine (they have existed since time immemorial).  I think they were added to avoid cases of if/else blocks that were otherwise completely empty if $SETUP or $CLEANUP were empty.\n\nThe only improvement might be to move those default values into init_testenv() instead of in each test script.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
